## Workflow Sequence Diagram

The following diagram shows the full lifecycle from initial idea to submission-ready manuscript, including the pre-draft quality gates, the per-chapter quality loop, and the post-draft feedback cycle.

> **Split diagrams** — individual sections are in `diagrams/`:
>
> | File | Sections |
> |---|---|
> | [diagrams/SEQ_01_SETUP_CONCEPT.puml](diagrams/SEQ_01_SETUP_CONCEPT.puml) | Session Start · Setup · Concept |
> | [diagrams/SEQ_02_STORY_STRUCTURE.puml](diagrams/SEQ_02_STORY_STRUCTURE.puml) | Story Structure |
> | [diagrams/SEQ_03_PRE_DRAFT.puml](diagrams/SEQ_03_PRE_DRAFT.puml) | Pre-Draft Gate · Outline Review |
> | [diagrams/SEQ_04_DRAFTING_LOOP.puml](diagrams/SEQ_04_DRAFTING_LOOP.puml) | Drafting Loop |
> | [diagrams/SEQ_05_POST_DRAFT_FEEDBACK.puml](diagrams/SEQ_05_POST_DRAFT_FEEDBACK.puml) | Post-Draft Review · Feedback Cycle · Series Update |
> | [diagrams/SEQ_06_SUBMISSION.puml](diagrams/SEQ_06_SUBMISSION.puml) | Submission · Audiobook |

```plantuml
@startuml fiction-book-writing-workflow

skinparam backgroundColor #FAFAFA
skinparam sequenceArrowThickness 2
skinparam roundcorner 8
skinparam sequenceParticipantBorderColor #555555
skinparam sequenceParticipantBackgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam noteBorderColor #AAAAAA
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #FFFFF0

actor Author
participant "speckit.help" as HLP #Gainsboro
participant "speckit.constitution" as C #LightSkyBlue
participant "speckit.specify" as SP #LightSkyBlue
participant "speckit.clarify" as CL #LightSkyBlue
participant "speckit.plan" as PL #LightGreen
participant "speckit.pov" as POV #LightGreen
participant "speckit.tasks" as TK #LightGreen
participant "speckit.analyze" as AN #LightYellow
participant "speckit.outline" as OL #LightGoldenRodYellow
participant "speckit.implement" as IM #LightCoral
participant "speckit.checklist" as CH #LightSalmon
participant "speckit.continuity" as CO #LightSalmon
participant "speckit.revise" as RV #LightSalmon
participant "speckit.polish" as PO #Thistle
participant "speckit.versions" as VER #Wheat
participant "speckit.glossary" as GL #Wheat
participant "speckit.research" as RS #Wheat
participant "speckit.subplot" as SUB #Bisque
participant "speckit.feedback" as FB #PeachPuff
participant "speckit.series" as SER #LightCyan
participant "speckit.brainstorm" as BRN #LavenderBlush
participant "speckit.interview" as INT #MistyRose
participant "speckit.roleplay" as RPL #Linen
participant "speckit.query" as QR #Lavender
participant "speckit.synopsis" as SYN #Honeydew
participant "speckit.pacing" as PAC #PaleGreen
participant "speckit.sensitivity" as SEN #LightPink
participant "speckit.export" as EX #Lavender

== Session Start ==

note over Author, HLP
  Run at any time to get
  workflow guidance and
  next-step recommendations.
end note

Author -> HLP: (any time)
HLP --> Author: phase detection + blockers + next action

== Setup ==

Author -> C: style mode + plot structure
C --> Author: constitution.md (Story Bible)

== Concept ==

opt Brainstorm first (any topic)
  Author -> BRN: topic (spec / plan / characters / themes / world / pov / ...)
  BRN --> Author: brainstorm notes file + optional patch to topic file
  note right of BRN
    Use before speckit.specify to
    explore ideas, or at any phase
    to stress-test existing decisions
    (challenge mode).
  end note
end

Author -> SP: free-text story idea
SP --> Author: spec.md (brief, arcs, beats)

Author -> CL: (implicit)
CL -> CL: scan for [NEEDS CLARIFICATION]
CL --> Author: resolved spec.md

note right of CL
  Resolve ALL ambiguities
  before planning. Gaps here
  become structural holes.
end note

== Story Structure ==

Author -> PL: (reads spec.md + constitution.md)
PL --> Author: plan.md (act breakdown, chapter map)
PL --> Author: research.md, glossary.md, characters/, locations.md, timeline.md

opt Series (non-standalone)
  Author -> SER: init
  SER --> Author: series/series-bible.md (scaffolded)
end

opt Character exploration (interview)
  Author -> INT: [character name]
  INT --> Author: conversation transcript + insight notes
end

opt Brainstorm story structure
  Author -> BRN: plan / characters / themes / world-building
  BRN --> Author: brainstorm notes + optional patch to plan/spec
end

opt Multi-POV Novel
  Author -> POV: draft
  POV --> Author: pov-structure.md (schedule, voices, asymmetry map)
  Author -> POV: audit / schedule / asymmetry / relay
  POV --> Author: updated pov-structure.md
end

Author -> TK: (reads plan.md + spec.md)
TK --> Author: tasks.md (scene tasks ordered by act + arc)

== Pre-Draft Gate ==

Author -> AN: (reads spec.md + plan.md + tasks.md)
AN --> Author: structural alignment report (read-only)

note right of AN
  Gaps flagged here must be
  fixed before drafting.
  No file modifications made.
end note

alt Gaps found
  Author -> PL: fix plan
  Author -> TK: regenerate tasks
  Author -> AN: re-analyze
end

== Outline Review ==

Author -> OL: all (or chapter range)
OL --> Author: outlines/<CHAPTER_ID>-outline.md (status: DRAFT)

note right of OL
  Author edits beat sequence,
  sensory anchors, dialogue reqs.
  Set APPROVED to allow AI drafting.
  Set SKIP to write chapter themselves.
end note

== Drafting Loop (per chapter) ==

loop for each chapter in tasks.md

  alt Outline APPROVED (AI drafts)
    Author -> IM: execute next task
    IM --> Author: draft/<CHAPTER_ID>.md
  else Outline SKIP (author writes)
    Author -> IM: --outline-only (optional)
    IM --> Author: outline file only (no prose)
    note right of IM
      Author writes draft/<CHAPTER_ID>.md
      manually, then runs checklist.
    end note
  end

  Author -> CH: (on draft chapter)
  CH --> Author: checklists/<CHAPTER_ID>-checklist.md

  alt Checklist FAIL
    Author -> RV: <CHAPTER_ID> [failure codes]
    RV --> Author: <CHAPTER_ID>_v2.md + diff summary
    Author -> CH: re-run checklist
  end

  opt Roleplay (scene exploration / dialog workshop)
    Author -> RPL: [chapter or outline reference]
    RPL --> Author: revision notes + subtext insights
    note right of RPL
      Walk through beats beat-by-beat
      with AI/user role assignments.
      Feeds back into revise or outline.
    end note
  end

  Author -> PO: (after checklist PASS)
  PO --> Author: <CHAPTER_ID>_polished.md

  Author -> GL: audit (find unregistered terms)
  GL --> Author: unregistered term candidates
  Author -> GL: add [term] (register new terms)

  opt Subplot management
    Author -> SUB: add [character] (new mid-draft arc)
    SUB --> Author: SP-NNN block added to subplots.md
    Author -> SUB: check (beat gaps / arc absence audit)
    SUB --> Author: CRITICAL / WARNING / INFO items
  end

  Author -> RS: check <CHAPTER_ID> (verify factual claims)
  RS --> Author: UNSUPPORTED / PENDING flags

  Author -> VER: diff <CHAPTER_ID> (review what changed)
  VER --> Author: narrative passage comparison

end

== Post-Draft Review ==

Author -> CO: (full manuscript or chapter range)
CO --> Author: continuity report (read-only)

opt Pacing / tension arc audit
  Author -> PAC: (full draft or chapter range)
  PAC --> Author: pacing-arc.md (Mermaid xychart + chapter score table)
  note right of PAC
    CRITICAL: sagging middle, undersold
    climax, premature peak.
    WARNING: false plateau, hook failure.
    Read-only; feeds speckit.revise.
  end note
end

opt Sensitivity / representation review
  Author -> SEN: (full draft, chapter, or --category)
  SEN --> Author: flagged report (CRITICAL / WARNING / NOTE)
  note right of SEN
    Covers: representation, harmful
    tropes, historical anachronism,
    language, trauma depictions.
    Read-only. Recommend human
    sensitivity reader before query.
  end note
end

note right of CO
  Story bible violations =
  automatic CRITICAL.
  No file modifications made.
end note

alt Continuity issues found
  Author -> RV: targeted chapter revision
  Author -> CO: re-run continuity
end

== Feedback Cycle (optional) ==

Author -> FB: feedback notes + reader type
FB --> Author: feedback/<reader>-<date>.md + revision tasks appended to tasks.md

note right of FB
  Reader-slug-prefixed task IDs
  prevent collisions across
  multiple feedback rounds.
end note

loop for each CRITICAL revision task
  Author -> RV: targeted revision
  Author -> CO: verify fix
end

Author -> VER: tag <CHAPTER_ID> vN <milestone>
VER --> Author: milestone label written to YAML frontmatter

== Series Update (after book completion) ==

opt Non-standalone
  Author -> SER: update [N]
  SER --> Author: series-bible.md updated (character states, new canon, threads)
end

== Submission ==

Author -> SYN: draft (or update post-draft)
SYN --> Author: synopsis.md (one-page 250–350w + full 1,000–2,000w)

note right of SYN
  Both formats reveal the ending.
  Run after plan (outline) or
  after drafting (accuracy).
  Required before query letter.
end note

Author -> QR: draft
QR --> Author: query-letter.md (250–350 words)

Author -> QR: update / track / comp-titles
QR --> Author: submission tracker updated

Author -> EX: docx / epub / latex
EX --> Author: submission-ready manuscript file

@enduml


